OL,7,FIn the little spare time she has,
OL,8,F16-year-old Daria Fesun paints
OL,9,Fpictures. The rainbow-coloured
OL,10,Fstill-lifes of vases filled with
OL,11,Fsunflowers and corn distance her from
OL,12,Fthe dismal reality of a year of war in
OL,13,FZaporizhzhia, Ukraine.
OL,15,FEvery day, Daria studies online at
OL,16,Fhome. Air raid alarms interrupt her
OL,17,Flessons, sometimes several times a day.
OL,18,FThen she and her younger sister shelter
OL,19,Fin a corridor, often for an hour or
OL,20,Flonger.
OL,3,CSecret phone apps and turning down
OL,4,Cbribes: How 'heroic' Ukrainian children
OL,5,Care resisting Russia
